---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import SectionHeading from '../components/SectionHeading.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';

const lastUpdated = 'July 17, 2026';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy and Data Use | YK Apparels"
  description="How YK Apparels collects, uses and protects your personal data, and the rights you have under GDPR, CCPA and other privacy laws."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 pt-16 pb-20 sm:px-8 lg:pt-20">
    <SectionHeading as="h1" eyebrow="Legal" title="Privacy Policy" lead={`Last updated: ${lastUpdated}`} />

    <div class="prose-legal mt-10">
      <p>
        YK Apparels ("we", "us", "our") respects your privacy. This policy explains what personal
        data we collect through <strong>ykapparels.com</strong>, how we use it, and the rights you
        have — wherever in the world you are contacting us from.
      </p>

      <h2>The short version</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>We only collect the information you choose to send us through our inquiry form or by contacting us directly.</li>
        <li>We use it for one purpose: responding to you and working on your production inquiry.</li>
        <li>We use <strong>no advertising and no tracking without your consent</strong>. Analytics cookies run only if you opt in via our consent banner — and the site works fully if you decline.</li>
        <li>We never sell, rent or trade your personal information. To anyone.</li>
        <li>We do not use automated decision-making or profiling.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Who we are (data controller)</h2>
      <p>
        YK Apparels, {site.address.street}, {site.address.city}, {site.address.country}.<br />
        Privacy contact: <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>
      </p>

      <h2>What we collect and why</h2>
      <h3>1. Inquiry form</h3>
      <p>
        When you submit our contact form we receive the details you enter: your name, brand or
        company, email address, country, product interest, estimated quantity and message. We use
        this solely to respond to your inquiry, prepare quotations and manage the resulting
        business relationship.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Legal basis (GDPR):</strong> taking pre-contractual steps at your request
        (Art. 6(1)(b)) — you are contacting a manufacturer about producing goods, and we process
        your details to answer that request. The checkbox on the form records your informed
        acknowledgment of this policy. Where Art. 6(1)(b) does not apply (for example, general
        questions unrelated to an order), we rely on our legitimate interest in responding to
        correspondence addressed to us (Art. 6(1)(f)), against which you may object at any time.
      </p>
      <h3>2. Direct contact</h3>
      <p>
        If you email, phone or WhatsApp us, we process the contact details and message content you
        provide in order to reply. WhatsApp is a service of Meta Platforms; their own privacy
        policy applies to the transmission of messages on their platform.
      </p>
      <h3>3. Technical data</h3>
      <p>
        Our hosting infrastructure keeps standard server logs (IP address, request time, user
        agent) for security and operations (legitimate interest, Art. 6(1)(f)). These are not used
        to profile visitors and are retained only briefly. Your theme preference (light/dark) and
        your cookie choice are stored locally in your own browser and never leave your device.
      </p>
      <h3>4. Analytics (only with your consent)</h3>
      <p>
        If — and only if — you click "Accept analytics" on our consent banner, we use
        <strong>Google Analytics 4</strong> (Google LLC / Google Ireland Ltd.) to understand how
        visitors use the site: pages viewed, approximate region, device type. Before you consent,
        no analytics code loads and no analytics cookies are set (we use Google Consent Mode v2
        with all storage denied by default). <strong>Legal basis:</strong> your consent
        (Art. 6(1)(a)), which you can withdraw at any time via "Cookie settings" in the footer —
        withdrawal is as easy as giving consent.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies and tracking</h2>
      <p>
        This website sets no cookies by default. The only cookies it can ever set are Google
        Analytics cookies, and those require your prior opt-in via the consent banner. Declining
        (or ignoring) the banner leaves the site fully functional and cookie-free. You can change
        your choice at any time via "Cookie settings" in the footer of every page.
      </p>

      <h2>Who receives your data</h2>
      <p>Your inquiry data is handled by a small number of service providers acting on our behalf:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Web3Forms</strong> (United States) — relays your form submission to our email inbox.</li>
        <li><strong>Our email provider</strong> — stores the resulting correspondence.</li>
        <li><strong>Our hosting provider</strong> — serves this website and keeps standard server logs.</li>
        <li><strong>Google LLC / Google Ireland Ltd.</strong> — analytics, only if you have opted in via the consent banner.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We share personal data with no one else, unless required by law.</p>

      <h2>International transfers</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>We are located in Pakistan</strong>, so when you contact us your inquiry data is
        transferred to and processed in Pakistan, which has not received an EU adequacy decision.
        For visitors in the EU/EEA and UK, this transfer is based on Art. 49(1)(b) GDPR: it is
        necessary to take the pre-contractual steps you yourself request by sending us an inquiry.
        You are never obliged to use the form — but there is no way for a Pakistani manufacturer to
        answer your inquiry without receiving it in Pakistan.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our service providers may additionally process data in the United States or the European
        Union. Where GDPR applies, those transfers rely on the EU–US Data Privacy Framework, the
        EU Standard Contractual Clauses, or an adequacy decision, as applicable to each provider.
      </p>

      <h2>How long we keep it</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Inquiries that don't lead to an order:</strong> deleted no later than 24 months after our last exchange — or immediately on request.</li>
        <li><strong>Business and contractual records:</strong> retained for the periods required by commercial and tax law (typically up to 6 years).</li>
        <li><strong>Server logs:</strong> retained briefly (days to a few weeks) for security purposes.</li>
        <li><strong>Analytics data:</strong> if you opted in, retained in aggregate form per Google Analytics settings (14 months), and never merged with your inquiry data.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>No automated decision-making</h2>
      <p>
        We do not use your personal data for automated decision-making or profiling within the
        meaning of Art. 22 GDPR. Every inquiry is read and answered by a person.
      </p>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <h3>European Union & United Kingdom (GDPR / UK GDPR)</h3>
      <p>
        You have the right to access, rectify and erase your personal data; to restrict or object
        to its processing; to data portability; and to withdraw consent at any time without
        affecting prior processing. You may also lodge a complaint with your local supervisory
        authority. To exercise any right, email <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a> —
        we respond within one month.
      </p>
      <h3>United States (CCPA/CPRA and similar state laws)</h3>
      <p>
        The categories of personal information we collect are: <strong>identifiers</strong> (name,
        email, company, country) and <strong>commercial information</strong> (the inquiry details
        you provide) — and, only with your opt-in, <strong>internet activity</strong> (analytics
        data). California residents (and residents of states with similar laws) have the right to
        know what personal information we collect, to request its deletion or correction, and to
        non-discrimination for exercising those rights. <strong>We do not sell or share personal
        information</strong> as defined by the CCPA/CPRA, and have not done so in the preceding 12
        months, so there is nothing to opt out of. To exercise your rights, email us at the address
        above — you may also use an authorized agent; we will verify requests via the email address
        associated with your inquiry.
      </p>
      <h3>Other countries</h3>
      <p>
        We extend the same rights — access, correction, deletion and objection — to everyone who
        contacts us, including under Canada's PIPEDA, Australia's Privacy Act, and Pakistan's data
        protection framework. One email is enough.
      </p>

      <h2>Security</h2>
      <p>
        This site is served over HTTPS. Access to inquiry correspondence is limited to the people
        who need it to respond to you.
      </p>

      <h2>Children</h2>
      <p>
        This website is a business-to-business service and is not directed at children. We do not
        knowingly collect data from anyone under 16.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        If we add services that change how data is handled, we will update this policy and, where
        required, ask for your consent first — as we already do for analytics. The date at the top
        reflects the latest revision.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions or requests: <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a> or write to
        YK Apparels, {site.address.street}, {site.address.city}, {site.address.country}.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .prose-legal :global(h2) {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.45rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-top: 2.2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.7rem;
  }
  .prose-legal :global(h3) {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-top: 1.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }
  .prose-legal :global(p) {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--body);
    margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
  }
  .prose-legal :global(ul) {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 1.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
  }
  .prose-legal :global(li) {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--body);
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }
  .prose-legal :global(a) {
    color: var(--accent-2);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }
  .prose-legal :global(strong) {
    color: var(--ink);
  }
</style>
